    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="man_ej.00064.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Altnacraig</name>
                    <name type="place">Oban</name>
                    <date when="1880-06-09">June 9: 80</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

            <p>I have just heard from our general <choice>
                    <abbr>P. O</abbr>
                    <expan>Post Office</expan>
                </choice> that the clerk here was mistaken in her directions
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="man_ej.00193.jpg" type="recto"/> as to <hi
                    rend="underline">how</hi> to send a <choice>
                    <abbr>P.O.O</abbr>
                    <expan>post office order</expan>
                </choice> to you. I now enclose order for &#163;1. for "Leaves of Grass" which
                please direct to "Miss
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="man_ej.00194.jpg" type="verso"/> Macdonald, c/o Professor Blackie, Oban, Scotland"</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>&amp; oblige yours gratefully</salute>
                <signed>Katie ES Macdonald.</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="man_ej.00066.jpg" type="recto"/>

        </body>
    </text>
